    "description": "Pericarditis is the inflammation of the pericardium, the thin, fibrous sac surrounding the heart. This condition can result from various causes, including viral infections, autoimmune diseases, or can occur postoperatively. It often presents with a sharp, pleuritic chest pain that may radiate to the neck, shoulders, or back, and can be exacerbated by lying down or taking deep breaths. Patients may also experience fever, fatigue, and a general feeling of malaise.",
